# ── Autonomous-worker scratch & runtime droppings ──────────────────────────────
# Workers write throwaway DB-probe scripts and runtime state that nothing pruned, so
# 700+ untracked files piled up in every `git status`. These rules stop the git noise;
# `npm run sweep:scratch` (+ the SessionStart hook) prunes them from disk. Every pattern
# below was verified to have ZERO collisions with tracked files (forensics 2026-06-09).

# Root-level ad-hoc scratch (root-anchored; verified 0 tracked root _* of any extension).
# Workers dump probe scripts (.mjs/.cjs) and payload/diff scratch (.json/.diff/...) here.
/_*.mjs
/_*.cjs
/_*.json
/_*.diff
/_*.txt
/_*.sh
/_*.sql

# .claude/ scratch probes + ad-hoc dumps (underscore-prefixed). 0 tracked .claude/_*.
.claude/_*
# Sweep throttle marker written by the SessionStart hook.
.claude/.scratch-sweep-last

# Timestamped / working backup dirs (git already provides versioning).
.claude/handoff-backup-*/
/.coord-sync-backup/
/.pre-pull-bak/

# Loose agent runtime-state JSON written at the repo root (per-tick, rewritten in place).
/.adam-chairman-decisions.json
/.adam-email-last.json
/.coord-email-last.json
/.coord-review-last.json
/docmon-report.json
# Per-account capacity gauge state (QF-20260720-406) — chairman-pasted usage readings
# keyed by accountUuid8, rewritten in place by lib/fleet/account-capacity-gauge.cjs
/.fleet-account-capacity.json

# Monitor PID files (scoped — do NOT blanket-ignore *.pid; .leo-dashboard.pid is tracked).
/.monitor-*.pid

# NOT ignored on purpose: scripts/one-off/_*, .rca/_*, .prd-payloads/, docs/plans/ — each
# holds tracked _-prefixed deliverables / plan docs where the prefix does NOT distinguish
# junk from real work. Triage those by hand (mirrored in the sweep script's exclude-list).

